apiOperationDetail.apiDesc:
 Returns an element whose id property matches the idName parameter. Provides
		 the ability to apply a style based on the id. 


For example, the following line sets the style "color" to 0xFF0000 (red), for the
		 element having the id span1.


		 textFlow.getElementByID("span1").setStyle("color", 0xFF0000);



Note: In the following code, p.addChild(s) removes s 
		 from its original parent and adds it to p, the new parent.


		 var s:SpanElement = new SpanElement();
		 var p:ParagraphElement = new ParagraphElement();
		 ...
		 s = textFlow.getElementByID("span3") as SpanElement;
		 p.addChild(s);
		 textFlow.addChild(p);

apiParam.apiDesc:
The type of the event. Event listeners can access this information through the
	 inherited type property. There is only one type of StatusChangeEvent: 
	 StatusChangeEvent.INLINE_GRAPHIC_STATUS_CHANGE;

The type of the event. Event listeners can access this information through the
	 inherited type property. There is only one type of SelectionEvent: 
	 SelectionEvent.SELECTION_CHANGE;
